            <abstract>
                <p>A miniature illustrating <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3612Miracle"/> typically 
                    with as a sequence of six episodes/events, showing: first, Bārok sitting in his house surrounded by those for whom he makes a feast; second, his guests
                    sitting and drinking wine; third, the icon of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref>; fourth, Bārok being consecrated as a monk; fifth,
                Bārok surrounded by his attackers who are holding various weapons; sixth, the funeral of Bārok.</p>
                <p>Images available at <ref target="https://pemm.princeton.edu/en-us/paintings/by-story/140">https://pemm.princeton.edu/en-us/paintings/by-story/140</ref></p>
